caption: All things considered, it's a good, local place to eat tasty wings despite being unreasonably expensive for what you get.  Their extra crispy garlic parmesan wings were a little too oily, but we're still appropriately flavorful.

Good taste. I liked how you could split orders by sauce and select how many wings per each sauce. Lemon pepper sauce was really peppery. Wings were small. Ordering them crunchy is 👍🏼👍🏼👍🏼 The gyro was not bad but nothing special either. Good mask practices, really appreciated, I'll be back.

Today was my first time, I ordered 10 wings, crispy, with medium sauce.  It wasn't quite what I was expecting,  The wings had the relatively thick sauce poured over them after being placed in the to go box and were not tossed and coated in the sauce.  I agree with a previous review that the sauce was brown and gritty and was not a typical red buffalo sauce. I did not care for the sauce, I ended up scraping it off after the first two wings. I also had several wings with broken bones and two were broken through and just partial wings.  The blue cheese dressing also was a little different, had a brown tint to it and also seemed more gritty than smooth and creamy with chunks of blue cheese. I will say the wings were cooked nicely and were crispy on the outside.  If I were go back I would probably order the crispy wings with not sauce and see if they just has something like Franks Red Hot if I really wanted a sauce. Service was fine as I just picked up a to go order.

First off, the sauces are very odd, maybe unique , but the medium sauce was brown and gritty and just weird to eat. Next, the majority of bones were broken, I eat alot of wings and have never seen so many broken bones. It was to the pint you probably wouldn't want a child eating the wings. Finally, the upset stomach afterwards was not pleasant. The service was friendly which saved it a star but this is a place to avoid.

The wings were old and dry, just horrible and the subs were not the old style, were dry and had no flavor! Not juicy or even warm.. My family knows a good Philly and that last night was the opposite of that. The woman on the phone was very curt and not nice at all so I should have taken that as a sign. It cost a few bucks that’s for sure but this family will never go to that restaurant for anything ever again. Talk about a nose dive, this food was as bad as it gets, I had to toss most of it and make frozen nuggets instead. My advice to you Wings n Things on arctic and 36th is if you’re not going to care anymore and treat your customers this way, you should probably just roll up your operation before you destroy your reputation completely and anger the community with bad service and even worse food. Let somebody else have a business there and we’ll just chalk it up to “was nice while it lasted” overall I give one star!

I’ve been ordering wings from Wings N’ Things for over a decade and have appreciated their consistency over the years.  Their wings are what they’re best at: Crispy, sauced and/or rubbed, either in Teryaki, Garlic Parm (my favorite), Mild, Hot, Extra Hot or Nuke (some of the hottest in town). Often, I find that some wings from other places are soggy and drowning in sauce, whereas these guys offer a crispy but flavorful alternative.  If you are looking for something other than the same ol’ Chinese or (Sicily’s) Pizza, give these guys a shot.

I lived in Anchorage from 1982 - 1992. My father used to order from the old, downtown Wings 'N' Things all of the time. Wings 'N' Things nights were some of my favorites, and after I left Alaska, those wings haunted my memories. I've tried hundreds of other restaurants' buffalo wings hoping for something like the wings of my childhood, but nothing has quite been the same.  Came back to Alaska this week for the first time since ~1995 and I'm happy to report that, other than this being a different Wings 'N' Things with a different location run by different owners, nothing has changed. The recipe is the same, these are the wings of my childhood.  They say you can't go home again, but today, I did. Thanks WnT!

I adore these wings. I first tried them when some coworkers ordered a bunch  and I've loved them ever since. I can see why some people wouldn't like all the sauce and their small size, but they're perfect for me. One of the things that makes them my favorite is the lack of fat in their wings, which is mostly due to their small size. I hate fatty chicken wings and have never found another place besides Wings'N Things where this isn't a problem. It also helps that I love the unique sauce, so I don't consider the fact that the wings practically swim in it as being undesirable. I eat them regularly and have never gotten ill from it, and neither has anyone else I know.

I picked up lunch for the office today we had ordered 40 wings and they came out horrible. They had this brown caked on thick nasty sauce laying in a quarter inch of oil. They were inedible had a bad smell and taste to them. Everyone that ate just one ended up in the bathroom after just eating one. When contacting the manager her customer service was just as bad as her wings. She argued with me as a customer, saying that everybody loves their wings.  We've been going to Wings-N-Things for over 20 years now, we've had a few times where the food was not up to par, but this time took the cake.  We ended up not being able to eat lunch, and the manager wouldn't even let us bring them back.  The manager was going to call us back, but it's been several hours since our initial call to her letting her know about our dissatisfaction.  We ended up going to Costco and getting chicken bakes for lunch for the office.  Having drove across town to get Wings-N-Things, not only was it a waste of time, & money, but also a waste of gas.  20 years of coming back to Wings-N-Things all down the drain.  We WILL NOT be going back to them.
